{{Football club infobox | clubname = Al-Ittihad SC| image = | fullname = Al-Ittihad Sport Club| founded = {{Start date and age|1937}} | ground = Al-Ittihad stadium| capacity = | owner = | chairman = Dr. Sabah Mahdi | manager = | league = [[Iraq Division 1|Iraq Division One]] | season = | position = | website = https://web.facebook.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D9%81%D8%AD%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%87-%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%8A-1819225285012552/?_rdc=1&_rdr | <!--Home Shirt--> | pattern_la1 = _shoulder_stripes_white_stripes | pattern_b1 = _mli1012h | pattern_ra1 = _shoulder_stripes_white_stripes | pattern_sh1 = | pattern_so1 = _ | leftarm1 = F8DE7E | body1 = F8DE7E | rightarm1 = F8DE7E | shorts1 = F8DE7E | socks1 = FFFFFF | pattern_la2 = _whiteborder | pattern_b2 = _airdrie1213a | pattern_ra2 = _whiteborder | pattern_sh2 = | pattern_so2 = _ | leftarm2 = 0000FF | body2 = 0000FF | rightarm2 = 0000FF | shorts2 = 0000FF | socks2 = FFFFFF }}
'''Al-Ittihad Sport Club''' ({{lang-ar|'''نادي الاتحاد الرياضي'''}}), is an [[Iraq]]i [[multi-sport club]] based in Al-Ashar, [[Basra]].
==History== Al-Ittihad was founded in 1937, is third sport club that become established in [[Iraq]] after [[Al-Tayaran]] and [[Al-Minaa]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraqfound.html Iraq Clubs- Foundation Dates]</ref> Since [[1976–77 Iraqi National League|1976 season]] the club was playing in the [[Iraqi Premier League|Iraqi League]]<ref>[http://www.niiiis.com/76-77.html History of Iraqi league, 1976–77 ''(in Arabic)'']</ref> in three seasons,<ref>[http://www.niiiis.com/77-78.html History of Iraqi league, 1977–78 ''(in Arabic)'']</ref> then relegated [[Iraq Division 1|Iraq Division One]] in [[1978–79 Iraqi National League|1979 season]].<ref>[http://www.niiiis.com/78-79.html History of Iraqi league, 1978–79 ''(in Arabic)'']</ref>
The club played in Iraq Division one and won this championship in 1980–81 season and promoted in the league again and played [[1981–82 Iraqi National League|1981–82 season]] in league.<ref>[http://www.niiiis.com/81-82.html History of Iraqi league, 1981–82 ''(in Arabic)'']</ref>
==Honours== *'''[[Iraq Division One]]''' **'''Winner (1):''' 1980–81
