'''National High School Games''' ({{zh|t=全國中等學校運動會|s=全国中等学校运动会|p=Quánguó Zhōngděng Xuéxiào Yùndònghuì|first=t}}) is the largest [[multi-sport event]] for junior and senior high school players in Taiwan. The Games started in 1952, under the name of '''Taiwan Provincial High School Games''' ({{zh|t=臺灣省中學運動會|s=台湾省中学运动会|p=Táiwānshěng Xuéxiào Yùndònghuì|first=t}}). It is now controlled by [[Ministry of Education (Republic of China)|Ministry of Education]] and National Sports Council, [[Executive Yuan]]. The host city changes every year. The name "National High School Game" has been officially used since the administration district restructured in 2000.
==Sports== The following sports are National High School Games official programs: * [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] * [[Archery]] * [[Badminton]] * [[Football (soccer)]] * [[Gymnastics]] * [[Team handball|Handball]] * [[Judo]] * [[Karate]] * [[Martial arts]] * [[Soft tennis]] * [[Swimming (sport)|Swimming]] * [[Table tennis]] * [[Taekwondo]] * [[Tennis]] * [[Powerlifting|Weightlifting]] * [[Wrestling]]
==Results== ===Football (soccer)=== The football (soccer) program at the National High School Games is probably the most important event for high school football teams in Taiwan. In each group, 8 teams are selected to compete in the final round after playing in the qualifying tournaments.
